(83, 'Lullaby of Birdland', '', 'Eb', 120, '4/4', 'swing', 23, 'The tune is in G major and uses mostly standard jazz harmony built around ii–V–I movements.\n\nCore harmonic devices:\n\nii–V–I in G: Am7 – D7 – Gmaj7\n\nSecondary ii–V progressions (e.g., Em7–A7, Dm7–G7)\n\nCircle of fifths motion\n\nOccasional dominant substitutions\n\nIntro', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, '[sbn_leadsheet title=\"Lullaby of Birdland\" key=\"Eb\" tempo=\"120\" time=\"4/4\" rhythm=\"swing\"]\n\n[A label=\"Intro\" breaks=\"4\"]\n| Cm7 F7       | Bb7 Eb7      | Ab13 Db13 G7 | G7           |\n\n[A breaks=\"4,4,2\"]\n| Cm6 Am7b5    | D7 G7        | Cm6 Am7b5    | Fm7 Bb7      |\n| Ebmaj7 Cm7   | Fm7 Bb7      | Ebmaj7       | Dm7b5 G7     |\n| Ebmaj7 Bb7   | Eb6          |\n\n[B breaks=\"4,4\"]\n| C7           | Fm7          | Fm7 Bb7      | Ebmaj7 G7    |\n| C7           | Fm7          | Fm7 Bb7      | Ebmaj7 G7    |\n\n[D label=\"Ending\" breaks=\"1\"]\n| Ebmaj7 Eb6   |\n\n\n[sbn_voicings]\nAm7b5: 5x554x @4\nBb7: 6x67xx @6\nC7@14.0: 8x89xx @8\nC7@18.0: 8x89xx @8\nCm6@4.0: 8x78xx @7\nCm6@6.0: 8x78xx @7\nCm7: x313xx\nD7@5.0: x545xx @4\nDm7b5: x5656x @5\nEbmaj7: x6878x @6\nF7: 1x12xx\nFm7: x868xx @6\nG7: 3x34xx @3\n[/sbn_voicings]\n\n[sbn_repeats]\n{\"4\":{\"start\":true},\"11\":{\"end\":true}}\n[/sbn_repeats]\n\n[sbn_endings]\n{\"10\":{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"start\",\"text\":\"1.\"},\"11\":{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"stop\",\"text\":\"1.\"},\"12\":{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"start\",\"text\":\"2.\"},\"13\":{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"stop\",\"text\":\"2.\"}}\n[/sbn_endings]\n\n[sbn_info]\n[description]\nThe tune is in G major and uses mostly standard jazz harmony built around ii–V–I movements.\n\nCore harmonic devices:\n\nii–V–I in G: Am7 – D7 – Gmaj7\n\nSecondary ii–V progressions (e.g., Em7–A7, Dm7–G7)\n\nCircle of fifths motion\n\nOccasional dominant substitutions\n\nIntro\n[/description]\n[/sbn_info]\n\n[/sbn_leadsheet]', '{\"title\":\"Lullaby of Birdland\",\"composer\":\"\",\"key\":\"Eb\",\"tempo\":120