(1, 'gilberto-rhythm', 'Gilberto Rhythm', 'João Gilberto shaped the modern Bossa Nova guitar style. He often played a simple rhythm, that he destilled from the more complex patterns of Samba music. His playing combines a steady bass pulse (thumb) with off-beat, syncopated chord plucks (fingers).', 'brazilian', '2/4', 8, 'x.x..x..', 'x...x...', 87, '', 'chega173.mp3', 1, 1, '2026-01-22 09:45:43', '2026-03-07 13:13:14', 'sixteenth', 'none', 'tamborim', 'kick'),
